Sure, here are some examples of sentences in Serbian that use the word "megi" in different forms and positions:

1. *Megi* je danas bila kod mene u poseti. (Megi visited me today.)
2. Danas sam video *megija* kako trči po livadi. (Today, I saw a hare running in the meadow.)
3. Mama je upalila *megiće* na jelci. (Mom turned on the Christmas tree lights.)
4. *Megi* mi je pokazala novu igricu na telefonu. (Megi showed me a new game on her phone.)
5. Naši planovi su propali jer je *megi* otkazala dolazak. (Our plans fell through because Megi canceled her visit.)

In these sentences, "megi" is used in different forms and positions, including as a proper name, a noun, and as an adjective. The star (*) marks the word "megi" in each sentence.